  "prompt": "Is it okay for an Indian to travel from USA to India via Brussels with expired US visa?",
  "response": "Traveling from the USA to India via Brussels with an expired US visa can present challenges. Here are a few considerations:\n\n1. **Traveling to Belgium**: You generally need a valid visa to enter Belgium if you're making a stopover there. If you have an expired US visa, it usually does not impact your transiting through Belgium, but you should check whether you need a transit visa based on your nationality and the specific airport policies.\n\n2. **Boarding Your Flight**: Airlines may require you to have a valid visa for your destination or any transit countries when you board a flight. If your US visa is expired, some airlines may deny you boarding, especially if the itinerary involves a stop in the USA after Brussels.\n\n3. **Returning to India**: If you're traveling back to India, make sure all your Indian documentation is in order, including your Indian passport and any required visas if applicable.\n\n4. **Consult with Authorities**: It\u2019s always best to consult your airline and possibly check with the Belgian consulate or immigration services for the most accurate and updated information concerning travel regulations.\n\nMake sure to resolve any potential issues before booking your travel and ensure that you have all necessary documents for your journey.",
